task: Implement BB #39: Agent-first stack migration to Go control plane. Create Go 1.25.x project structure with modules: internal/sprite, internal/lifecycle, internal/dispatch, internal/contracts, cmd/bb. Implement bb CLI with Cobra. Create machine contracts (JSON/NDJSON outputs, explicit error codes). Port critical shell scripts to Go with idempotent operations. Add comprehensive tests. Issue: https://github.com/misty-step/bitterblossom/issues/39

Implement BB #40: Scaffold Go bb CLI and control-plane module boundaries. Create go.mod (Go 1.25.x), project layout with internal/sprite, internal/lifecycle, internal/dispatch, internal/contracts, cmd/bb. Implement command stubs matching current shell scripts. Add compatibility wrappers. Acceptance: bb --help lists commands, go test ./... passes, legacy scripts delegate to bb. Issue: https://github.com/misty-step/bitterblossom/issues/40

Implement BB #43: Port dispatch/watchdog to Go state-machine supervision. Port Ralph loop orchestration, watchdog health/staleness detection to explicit state transitions. Replace fragile process handling with tracked metadata. Emit structured events (started, heartbeat, blocked, complete, stale, error). Add state-machine tests for transitions. Acceptance: dispatch + watchdog run from bb with deterministic status, regression tests for fragility cases. Issue: https://github.com/misty-step/bitterblossom/issues/43
